Reasoning: The paper deals with computational primitives using DNA self-assembly, which is a topic that falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves computational complexity analysis, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of tile assembly models and geometric algorithms for DNA self-assembly could also place the paper under the sub-categories of computational geometry (cs.CG) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper proposes a method to compute irrational numbers, which could potentially fall under the sub-category of scientific computing (cs.SC).
